
# SCOPE OF WORK

MHS requests the following services:

# Cybersecurity Program Assessment

Conduct a current-state cybersecurity assessment aligned to NIST CSF and NIST SP 800-53

Identify gaps in governance, risk management, and technical controls

Assess risks related to EHR systems, medical devices, cloud services, and remote access

# Program Design & Framework Alignment

Develop a target-state cybersecurity program aligned with:

NIST Cybersecurity Framework (Identify, Protect, Detect, Respond, Recover)

Healthcare regulatory requirements (HIPAA, HITECH)

Define cybersecurity policies, standards, and procedures

Establish a cybersecurity governance model and risk management processes

# Risk Management & Controls Implementation

Develop a cybersecurity risk register and risk treatment plans

Recommend and prioritize security controls based on risk appetite

Address remote workforce security (MFA, endpoint security, VPN, zero trust concepts)

# Incident Response & Resilience

Develop or enhance Incident Response and Breach Notification Plans

Align response procedures with NIST SP 800-61

Support disaster recovery and business continuity planning

# Training & Awareness

Design a cybersecurity awareness program for all employees

Provide specialized training for IT, clinical staff, and remote workers

Conduct phishing awareness and tabletop exercises

# Deliverables

The selected vendor will provide:

NIST CSF Gap Assessment Report

Cybersecurity Governance Framework

Enterprise Risk Register and Risk Treatment Plan

Updated cybersecurity policies and procedures

Incident Response and Business Continuity documentation

Cybersecurity roadmap with prioritized initiatives (12–24 months)

# Regulatory & Standards Alignment

The cybersecurity program must align with:

NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF)

NIST SP 800-53 / 800-171

HIPAA Security Rule

HITECH Act

Applicable state healthcare privacy regulations

# Project Timeline

MHS anticipates a phased engagement:

Phase 1: Assessment & Gap Analysis (6–8 weeks)

Phase 2: Program Design & Roadmap (6 weeks)

Phase 3: Implementation Support & Training (as required)

# Vendor Qualifications

MHS seeks a vendor with:

Proven experience in healthcare cybersecurity

Demonstrated expertise in NIST frameworks

Knowledge of HIPAA and healthcare regulatory requirements

Experience securing remote workforce environments

# Success Criteria

The engagement will be considered successful when:

A NIST-aligned cybersecurity program is fully documented

Cybersecurity risks are identified, prioritized, and managed

Compliance readiness is improved

MHS leadership has clear visibility into cybersecurity posture

# Conclusion

MedSure Health System looks forward to partnering with [Your Organization Name] to establish a mature, NIST-based cybersecurity program that protects patient data, supports clinical operations, and strengthens organizational resilience against evolving cyber threats.